10 AstA^Hd *
He (a man, S) was, or became, alone, by himself, apart from others, or solitary;
syn. Ainofarada; (S, K;) as also ↓ A@t~aHada [written with the disjunctive alif Ait~aHada, originally Aiy^otaHada or AiwtaHada], (K, TA,) or tawaH~ada. (CK.) -A2- maA A@sotaA^oHada bihi He did not know it; did not know, or had not knowledge, of it; did not understand it; did not know the minute circumstances of it; or did not perceive it by any of the senses; syn. lamo ya$oEuro bihi; (L, K;) i. e., a thing, or an affair: of the dial. of El-Yemen. (L.)
